http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Naveen-pitches-for-world-class-sports-facilities-in-Odisha/article14000558.ece

Odisha Chief Minister Naveen Patnaik on Thursday directed the Sports Department of his government to prepare a blueprint to build world-class sporting facilities and improved infrastructure to host national and international sporting events in Odisha.Mr. Patnaik issued the direction while chairing a high-level meeting at the State Secretariat here.It was discussed in the meeting that Odisha did not have infrastructure of international standard for any other sport except hockey.The meeting decided to build infrastructures of international standard for football, track and field and other games. It was also decided to establish well-equipped mini-stadiums in different blocks, urban local bodies and cities across the State, Mr. Patnaik directed the authorities concerned to complete construction of 100 such stadiums by August this year.The construction of as many as 159 mini stadiums in rural areas and 41 in urban local body areas have been taken up so far.It has also been decided to complete construction of one minimum stadium each in all 111 municipalities and Notified Area Councils in the State within three years.Besides, it was decided to build four mini stadiums each in the five municipal corporations such as Bhubaneswar, Cuttack, Sambalpur, Berhampur and Rourkela every year.The meeting also decided to give responsibility to the Panchayati Raj Department to improve school sports grounds across the State along with the village sports grounds.